cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SI

The paper discusses attacks on generative models, which are commonly used in computer vision and machine learning applications. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the use of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) and Variational Autoencoders (VAEs), which are popular architectures in the fields of machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of these attacks for assessing model quality in machine learning as a service setups, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
